Recently I've come upon a body of literature which promotes colocleansing as a vital aid to preventive medicine through nutrition.  Iparticular, Dr. Bernard Jenssen in his book "Colon Cleansing foHealth and Longevity" -- the title actually escapes me, but it is versimilar to that -- claims that regular self-administered colonicsalong with certain orally ingested "debris-loosening agents", boostthe immune system to a significant degreeHe also plugs a unique appliance called the "Colema Board", whicfacilitates the self-administration of colonics.  It sells for ove$100 from a California-based company.  He also plugs Vitra-Toproducts as his chemical agents of choice: these include volcanic ashsupposedly for its electrical charge, and psyllium powder, for itbulkinessIf anyone knows anything about colon cleansing theory, itparticulars, or the Colema Board and related products, I'd be verinterested to hear about research and personal experienceThis article is crossposted to alt.magick as the issue touches upofasting and cleansing through a "ritual" system of purification-- El--/-------------------------------------------------------------------------\![wiesel@cs.yale.edu] Elisha Wiesel, Davenport College '94 Yale University!   ![wiesel@minerva.cis.yale.edu] (203) 436-1338<-School (212) 371-2756<-Home\\-------------------------------------------------------------------------